The paper discusses the problem of learning finite-state controllers for partially observable environments, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also mentions the use of stochastic gradient descent, which is a popular optimization technique in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
